      "content": "You can use the adult ibuprofen, but you must calculate the exact milligram dose based on his weight, not just guess \"smaller.\" If he weighs less than 40 pounds, you are strictly forbidden from giving him any ibuprofen at all. If he is heavier, give him 10 to 15 milligrams per kilogram of body weight every 6 to 8 hours. Do not wait for the fever to break before calling the doctor, because a high fever in an 8-year-old is a medical emergency that requires immediate professional intervention.",
